# Pulumi / Node build artifacts — never committed.
node_modules/
bin/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Pulumi keeps stack STATE in your configured backend (Pulumi Cloud or a self-managed
# backend), never in the repo. Per-stack config (Pulumi.<stack>.yaml) is created locally by
# `pulumi stack init` + `pulumi config set`; it may hold ENCRYPTED secrets and is intentionally
# left untracked here so real deploy config (the GitHub org/repo, the chosen region) isn't
# committed. Commit a Pulumi.<stack>.yaml deliberately only if it contains no secrets.
Pulumi.*.yaml
